description:
Data source: https://personal.broadinstitute.org/meuleman/reg2map/HoneyBadger2-impute_release/ Chromatin state discovery and characterization. 

Data were downloaded in R format. We included only intervals overlapping with DNaseI regions selected with -log10(p) >= 10. 

Information about the interpretation of each of the 25 states can be found here: http://egg2.wustl.edu/roadmap/web_portal/imputed.html#chr_imp. 

The name for each cell type can be found here: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/u/1/d/1yikGx4MsO9Ei36b64yOy9Vb6oPC5IBGlFbYEt-N6gOM/edit?usp=sharing#gid=15.

description:
Database for Nonsynonymous SNPs' functional predictions, v2.9.3.

The dbNSFP is an integrated database of functional annotations from multiple sources for the comprehensive collection of human non-synonymous SNPs (NSs).

Its current version includes a total of 87,361,054 NSs. It compiles prediction scores from 14 prediction algorithms (SIFT, Polyphen2, LRT, MutationTaster, MutationAssessor, FATHMM, MetaSVM, MetaLR, CADD, VEST, PROVEAN, M-CAP, Eigen\uff0cEigen PC), eight conservation scores (phyloP46way_primate, phyloP46way_placental, phyloP100way_vertebrate, phastCons46way_primate, phastCons46way_placental, phastCons100way_veterbrate, GERP++, and SiPhy) and other function annotations.

We included all the original annotations except for allele frequencies in 1000 genome and ExAC since these are covered in other annotations.

Note 1: Missing data is designated as ".".
Note 2: The three Uniprot entries are based on Polyphen-2 v2.2.2 annotations.
title: dbNSFP v2.9.3
publication: Liu, Xiaoming et al. "dbNSFP v3.0: A One-Stop Database of Functional Predictions and Annotations for Human Non-Synonymous and Splice Site SNVs." Human mutation 37.3 (2016): 235-241.

title: FATHMM_pred
description: If a FATHMMori score is <=-1.5 (or rankscore >=0.81415) the corresponding NS is predicted as "D(AMAGING)"; otherwise it is predicted as "T(OLERATED)". Multiple predictions separated by ";".

title: FATHMM_rankscore
description: FATHMMnew=-FATHMMori scores were ranked among all FATHMMnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of FATHMMnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (smallest) rankscore is presented. The scores range from 0 to 1.

title: FATHMM_score
description: FATHMM default score (weighted for human inherited-disease mutations with Disease Ontology) (FATHMMori). Scores range from -18.09 to 11.0. The smaller the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. Multiple scores separated by ";" Please refer to Shihab et al. (2013) Human Mutation 34(1):57-65 for details.

title: GERP_RS
description: GERP++ RS score, the larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: GERP_RS_rankscore
description: GERP++ RS scores were ranked among all GERP++ RS scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of GERP++ RS scores in dbNSFP.

title: LRT_converted_rankscore
description: LRTori scores were first converted as LRTnew=1-LRTori*0.5 if Omega<1, or LRTnew=LRTori*0.5 if Omega>=1. Then LRTnew scores were ranked among all LRTnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank over the total number of the scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0.00166 to 0.85682.

title: LRT_omega
description: estimated nonsynonymous-to-synonymous-rate ratio (Omega, reported by LRT)

title: LRT_pred
description: LRT prediction, D(eleterious), N(eutral) or U(nknown), which is not solely determined by the score.

title: LRT_score
description: The original LRT two-sided p-value (LRTori), ranges from 0 to 1.

title: MCAP_pred
description: Prediction of M-CAP score based on the authors' recommendation, "T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.025.

title: MCAP_rankscore
description: M-CAP scores were ranked among all M-CAP scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of M-CAP scores in dbNSFP.

title: MCAP_score
description: M-CAP score (details in DOI: 10.1038/ng.3703). Scores range from 0 to 1. The larger the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect.

title: MetaLR_pred
description: Prediction of our MetaLR based ensemble prediction score,"T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.5. The rankscore cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.82268.

title: MetaLR_rankscore
description: MetaLR scores were ranked among all MetaLR scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MetaLR scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1.

title: MetaLR_score
description: Our logistic regression (LR) based ensemble prediction score, which incorporated 10 scores (SIFT, PolyPhen-2 HDIV, PolyPhen-2 HVAR, GERP++, MutationTaster, Mutation Assessor, FATHMM, LRT, SiPhy, phyloP) and the maximum frequency observed in the 1000 genomes populations. Larger value means the SNV is more likely to be damaging. Scores range from 0 to 1.

title: MetaSVM_pred
description: Prediction of our SVM based ensemble prediction score,"T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0. The rankscore cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.83357.

title: MetaSVM_rankscore
description: MetaSVM_rankscore: MetaSVM scores were ranked among all MetaSVM scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MetaSVM scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1.

title: MetaSVM_score
description: Our support vector machine (SVM) based ensemble prediction score, which incorporated 10 scores (SIFT, PolyPhen-2 HDIV, PolyPhen-2 HVAR, GERP++, MutationTaster, Mutation Assessor, FATHMM, LRT, SiPhy, phyloP) and the maximum frequency observed in the 1000 genomes populations. Larger value means the SNV is more likely to be damaging. Scores range from -2 to 3 in dbNSFP.

title: MutPred_AAchange
description: Amino acid change used for MutPred_score calculation.

title: MutPred_protID
description: UniProt accession or Ensembl transcript ID used for MutPred_score calculation.

title: MutPred_rankscore
description: MutPred scores were ranked among all MutPred scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MutPred scores in dbNSFP.

title: MutPred_score
description: General MutPred score. Scores range from 0 to 1. The larger the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect.

title: MutPred_top5features
description: Top 5 features (molecular mechanisms of disease) as predicted by MutPred with p values. MutPred_score > 0.5 and p < 0.05 are referred to as actionable hypotheses. MutPred_score > 0.75 and p < 0.05 are referred to as confident hypotheses. MutPred_score > 0.75 and p < 0.01 are referred to as very confident hypotheses.

title: MutationAssessor_pred
description: MutationAssessor's functional impact of a variant : predicted functional, i.e. high ("H") or medium ("M"), or predicted non-functional, i.e. low ("L") or neutral ("N"). The MAori score cutoffs between "H" and "M", "M" and "L", and "L" and "N", are 3.5, 1.935 and 0.8, respectively. The rankscore cutoffs between "H" and "M", "M" and "L", and "L" and "N", are 0.92924, 0.51945 and 0.19692, respectively.

title: MutationAssessor_rankscore
description: MAori scores were ranked among all MAori scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MAori scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1.

title: MutationAssessor_score
description: MutationAssessor functional impact combined score (MAori). The score ranges from -5.135 to 6.49 in dbNSFP. Please refer to Reva et al. (2011) Nucl. Acids Res. 39(17):e118 for details.

title: MutationTaster_converted_rankscore
description: The MTori scores were first converted: if the prediction is "A" or "D" MTnew=MTori; if the prediction is "N" or "P", MTnew=1-MTori. Then MTnew scores were ranked among all MTnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MTnew scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0.09067 to 0.80722.

title: MutationTaster_pred
description: MutationTaster prediction, "A" ("disease_causing_automatic"), "D" ("disease_causing"), "N" ("polymorphism") or "P" ("polymorphism_automatic"). The score cutoff between "D" and "N" is 0.5 for MTori and 0.31655 for the rankscore.

title: PROVEAN_converted_rankscore
description: PROVEANori were first converted to PROVEANnew=1-(PROVEANori+14)/28, then ranked among all PROVEANnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank the PROVEANnew score over the total number of PROVEANnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented.

title: PROVEAN_pred
description: If PROVEANori <= -2.5 (rankscore>=0.59) the corresponding NS is predicted as "D(amaging)"; otherwise it is predicted as "N(eutral)". Multiple predictions separated by ";"

title: PROVEAN_score
description: PROVEAN score (PROVEANori). Scores range from -14 to 14. The smaller the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. Multiple scores separated by ";". Details can be found in DOI: 10.1371/journal.pone.0046688

title: Polyphen2_HDIV_pred
description: Polyphen2 prediction based on HumDiv, "D" ("porobably damaging", HDIV score in [0.957,1] or rankscore in [0.52996,0.89917]), "P" ("possibly damaging", HDIV score in [0.453,0.956] or rankscore in [0.34412,0.52842]) and "B" ("benign", HDIV score in [0,0.452] or rankscore in [0.02656,0.34399]). Score cutoff for binary classification is 0.5 for HDIV score or 0.35411 for rankscore, i.e. the prediction is "neutral" if the HDIV score is smaller than 0.5 (rankscore is smaller than 0.35411), and "deleterious" if the HDIV score is larger than 0.5 (rankscore is larger than 0.35411). Multiple entries are separated by ";".

title: Polyphen2_HDIV_rankscore
description: Polyphen2 HDIV scores were first ranked among all HDIV scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank the score over the total number of the scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented. The scores range from 0.02656 to 0.89917.

title: Polyphen2_HDIV_score
description: Polyphen2 score based on HumDiv, i.e. hdiv_prob. The score ranges from 0 to 1. Multiple entries separated by ";".

title: Polyphen2_HVAR_pred
description: Polyphen2 prediction based on HumVar, "D" ("probably damaging", HVAR score in [0.909,1] or rankscore in [0.62955,0.9711]), "P" ("possibly damaging", HVAR in [0.447,0.908] or rankscore in [0.44359,0.62885]) and "B" ("benign", HVAR score in [0,0.446] or rankscore in [0.01281,0.44315]). Score cutoff for binary classification is 0.5 for HVAR score or 0.45998 for rankscore, i.e. the prediction is "neutral" if the HVAR score is smaller than 0.5 (rankscore is smaller than 0.45998), and "deleterious" if the HVAR score is larger than 0.5 (rankscore is larger than 0.45998). Multiple entries are separated by ";".

title: Polyphen2_HVAR_rankscore
description: Polyphen2 HVAR scores were first ranked among all HVAR scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank the score over the total number of the scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented. The scores range from 0.01281 to 0.9711.

title: Polyphen2_HVAR_score
description: Polyphen2 score based on HumVar, i.e. hvar_prob. The score ranges from 0 to 1. Multiple entries separated by \";\".

title: REVEL_rankscore
description: REVEL scores were ranked among all REVEL scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of REVEL scores in dbNSFP.

title: REVEL_score
description: REVEL is an ensemble score based on 13 individual scores for predicting the pathogenicity of missense variants. Scores range from 0 to 1. The larger the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. "REVEL scores are freely available for non-commercial use. For other uses, please contact Weiva Sieh" (weiva.sieh@mssm.edu)

title: SIFT_converted_rankscore
description: SIFTori scores were first converted to SIFTnew=1-SIFTori, then ranked among all SIFTnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank the SIFTnew score over the total number of SIFTnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores,o nly the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented. The rankscores range from 0.02654 to 0.87932.

title: SIFT_pred
description: If SIFTori is smaller than 0.05 (rankscore>0.55) the corresponding NS is predicted as "D(amaging)"; otherwise it is predicted as "T(olerated)". Multiple predictions separated by ";"

title: SIFT_score
description: SIFT score (SIFTori). Scores range from 0 to 1. The smaller the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. Multiple scores separated by ";".

title: SLR_test_statistic
description: SLR test statistic for testing natural selection on codons. A negative value indicates negative selection, and a positive value indicates positive selection. Larger magnitude of the value suggests stronger evidence.

title: SiPhy_29way_logOdds
description: SiPhy score based on 29 mammals genomes. The larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: SiPhy_29way_logOdds_rankscore
description: SiPhy_29way_logOdds scores were ranked among all SiPhy_29way_logOdds scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of SiPhy_29way_logOdds scores in dbNSFP.

title: SiPhy_29way_pi
description: The estimated stationary distribution of A, C, G and T at the site, using SiPhy algorithm based on 29 mammals genomes.

title: VEST3_rankscore
description: VEST3 scores were ranked among all VEST3 scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of VEST3 scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1. Please note VEST score is free for non-commercial use. For more details please refer to http://wiki.chasmsoftware.org/index.php/SoftwareLicense. Commercial users should contact the Johns Hopkins Technology Transfer office.

title: VEST3_score
description: VEST 3.0 score. Score ranges from 0 to 1. The larger the score the more likely the mutation may cause functional change. In case there are multiple scores for the same variant, the largest score (most damaging) is presented. Please refer to Carter et al., (2013) BMC Genomics. 14(3) 1-16 for details. Please note this score is free for non-commercial use. For more details please refer to http://wiki.chasmsoftware.org/index.php/SoftwareLicense. Commercial users should contact the Johns Hopkins Technology Transfer office.

title: aaalt
description: alternative amino acid; "." if the variant is a splicing site SNP (2bp on each end of an intron)

title: aapos
description: amino acid position as to the protein "-1" if the variant is a splicing site SNP (2bp on each end of an intron)

title: aapos_FATHMM
description: ENSP id and amino acid positions corresponding to FATHMM scores. Multiple entries separated by ";"

title: aapos_SIFT
description: ENSP id and amino acid positions corresponding to SIFT scores. Multiple entries separated by ";"

title: aaref
description: reference amino acid; "." if the variant is a splicing site SNP (2bp on each end of an intron)

title: ancestral_allele
description: Ancestral allele (based on 1000 genomes reference data). The following comes from its original README file: ACTG - high-confidence call, ancestral state supproted by the other two sequences; actg - low-confindence call, ancestral state supported by one sequence only; N - failure, the ancestral state is not supported by any other sequence; - - the extant species contains an insertion at this postion; . - no coverage in the alignment

title: clinvar_clinsig
description: clinical significance as to the clinvar data set 2 - Benign, 3 - Likely benign, 4 - Likely pathogenic, 5 - Pathogenic, 6 - drug response, 7 - histocompatibility. A negative score means the the score is for the ref allele

title: clinvar_golden_stars
description: ClinVar Review Status summary: 0 - no assertion criteria provided, 1 - criteria provided, single submitter, 2 - criteria provided, multiple submitters, no conflicts, 3 - reviewed by expert panel, 4 - practice guideline

title: clinvar_rs
description: rs number from the clinvar data set

title: clinvar_trait
description: the trait/disease the clinvar_clnsig referring to

title: cosmic_count
description: number of samples having this SNV in the COSMIC database

title: cosmic_id
description: ID of the SNV at the COSMIC (Catalogue Of Somatic Mutations In Cancer) database

title: genename
description: gene name; if the NScan be assigned to multiple genes, gene names are separated by ";"

title: hg18_pos
description: physical position on the chromosome as to hg18 (1-based coordinate)

title: hg38_chr
description: chromosome as to hg38, "." means the same as in the chr column

title: hg38_pos
description: physical position on the chromosome as to hg38 (1-based coordinate)

title: interpro_domain
description: domain or conserved site on which the variant locates. Domain annotations come from Interpro database. The number in the brackets following a specific domain is the count of times Interpro assigns the variant position to that domain, typically coming from different predicting databases. Multiple entries separated by ";".

title: phastCons100way_vertebrate
description: phastCons conservation score based on the multiple alignments of 100 vertebrate genomes (including human). The larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: phastCons100way_vertebrate_rankscore
description: phastCons100way_vertebrate scores were ranked among all phastCons100way_vertebrate scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of phastCons100way_vertebrate scores in dbNSFP.

title: phastCons46way_placental
description: phastCons conservation score based on the multiple alignments of 33 placental mammal genomes (including human). The larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: phastCons46way_placental_rankscore
description: phastCons46way_placental scores were ranked among all phastCons46way_placental scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of phastCons46way_placental scores in dbNSFP.

title: phastCons46way_primate
description: phastCons conservation score based on the multiple alignments of 10 primate genomes (including human). The larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: phastCons46way_primate_rankscore
description: phastCons46way_primate scores were ranked among all phastCons46way_primate scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of phastCons46way_primate scores in dbNSFP.

title: phyloP100way_vertebrate
description: phyloP (phylogenetic p-values) conservation score based on the multiple alignments of 100 vertebrate genomes (including human). The larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: phyloP100way_vertebrate_rankscore
description: phyloP100way_vertebrate scores were ranked among all phyloP100way_vertebrate scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of phyloP100way_vertebrate scores in dbNSFP.

title: phyloP46way_placental
description: phyloP (phylogenetic p-values) conservation score based on the multiple alignments of 33 placental mammal genomes (including human). The larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: phyloP46way_placental_rankscore
description: phyloP46way_placental scores were ranked among all phyloP46way_placental scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of phyloP46way_placental scores in dbNSFP.

title: phyloP46way_primate
description: phyloP (phylogenetic p-values) conservation score based on the multiple alignments of 10 primate genomes (including human). The larger the score, the more conserved the site.

title: phyloP46way_primate_rankscore
description: phyloP46way_primate scores were ranked among all phyloP46way_primate scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of phyloP46way_primate scores in dbNSFP.

title: reliability_index
description: Number of observed component scores (except the maximum frequency in the 1000 genomes populations) for MetaSVM and MetaLR. Ranges from 1 to 10. As MetaSVM and MetaLR scores are calculated based on imputed data, the less missing component scores, the higher the reliability of the scores and predictions.

The Genome Aggregation Database (gnomAD) is a resource developed by an international coalition of investigators, with the goal of aggregating and harmonizing both exome and genome sequencing data from a wide variety of large-scale sequencing projects, and making summary data available for the wider scientific community.
			
The data set provided on this website spans 123,136 exome sequences and 15,496 whole-genome sequences from unrelated individuals sequenced as part of various disease-specific and population genetic studies. 
			
The gnomAD Principal Investigators and groups that have contributed data to the current release are listed here: http://gnomad.broadinstitute.org/about
		
All data here are released for the benefit of the wider biomedical community, without restriction on use - see the terms of use here: http://gnomad.broadinstitute.org/terms
title: gnomAD
publication: Exome Aggregation Consortium et al. "Analysis of Protein-Coding Genetic Variation in 60,706 Humans." Nature 536.7616 (2016): 285-291.

description:
Data source: https://enhancer.lbl.gov/cgi-bin/imagedb3.pl?page_size=20000;show=1;search.result=yes;form=search;search.form=no;action=search;search.sequence=1 Validated enhancers from VISTA. We select only positive human elements. 

Once downloaded, 2APR2017, the data were processed as follows: 

'grep \">Human\" vista_2APR2017.txt | grep \"positive\" | awk '{split($0,a,\"|\"); print a[2], a[5]}' > vista_2APR2017_processed.txt'

More info available here: https://enhancer.lbl.gov/aboutproject_n.html.
